  "text": "Voluntary movements in the toes of the feet were initiated two weeks after surgery, and in the course of the following months, the patient showed clear and progressive motor improvement, being able to stand up with the help of canes one year after surgery, and pedal voluntarily on a stationary bike, but without being able to take steps. Supplementary Movie show the motor improvement obtained during the followup. The patient described also progressive increase in infralesional sensitivity and in bladder control, with a score of 5 in the Geffner scale [CITATION_1] one year after surgery.",
